# Review

Run review convergence for the active governed change.

## Invocation
```bash
slipway review
```

## Contract
- `review` is the explicit S3 review stage command.
- Evaluates artifact completeness, implementation quality, selected reviewer evidence, and plan/code alignment.
- When `slipway next --json` / `slipway run --json` returns a review batch,
  each `review_batch.skills[].subagent` directive is the host spawning contract
  for that reviewer. Honor its `model`, `allowed_skills`, and
  `allowed_mcp_servers` before dispatching the fresh review subagent; omitted
  fields inherit host defaults.
- Review feedback is repaired through `slipway fix`: dispatch a fresh-context repair subagent, record the affected reviewer evidence, then close by reviewer rereview.
- Same-intent scope gaps found during review are change amendments inside the current change.
- Intent conflict is not review alignment; surface `new_change_required:intent_conflict` and start a new governed change.
- Show review summary to user with pass/fail per layer.

## Flags
- `--all`: review all artifacts (overrides the changed-only default)
- `--changed-only`: restrict review to changed artifacts
- `--focus <alias>`: run a focus review (see `--list-focuses`)
- `--list-focuses`: list available review focuses
- `--format <text|json>`: output format for `--list-focuses`
- `--hydrate`: append selected hydrate reference bodies (text output only)
- `--hydrate-ref <skill-id>/<name>`: restrict `--hydrate` to the named reference (repeatable; requires `--hydrate`)
- `--json`: JSON output
- `--change <slug>`: target a specific active change
